      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Erd\\H{o}s and Rado proved that $\\mathfrak{c}\\to (\\omega+n,4)_2^3$ for any $2\\leq n<\\omega$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "624535468eb8ebb766c545dd11a0432ae05b8bea64e333ef0f38ed12d71b122a",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $\\mathfrak{c}$ be the ordinal of the real numbers, $\\beta$ be any countable ordinal, and $2\\leq n<\\omega$. Is it true that $\\mathfrak{c}\\to (\\beta, n)_2^3$?"
    }
